HEADWORD: Hydrographer
<hw>Hy*drog"ra*pher</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One skilled in
the hydrography; one who surveys, or draws maps or charts of, the sea,
lakes, or other waters, with the adjacent shores; one who describes the
sea or other waters.</def> <rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj></p>

